lyrics:
In alleys dark, where streetlights gleam,
Cats roam free, rulers of the scene.
With stealthy steps and piercing eyes,
They claim their turf under moonlit skies.
From rooftops high to hidden nooks,
Their empire spreads in shadowed nooks.

They prowl the streets, a silent force,
No obstacle can alter their course.
With whiskers twitching, tails held high,
They reign supreme beneath the sky.
From city blocks to rural lanes,
Their dominance forever reigns.

Through whispers low and feline grace,
They navigate this concrete maze.
With each meow, a declaration,
Of their conquest, no hesitation.
So heed the call of the urban beat,
For in this world, cats claim their seat.
